    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-11-24T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-11-24T16:00:00-05:00" n="730"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d730">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00112 European War 1939/9629: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Sweden</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-11-24T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >November 24, 1943—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1278. Embassy in London has been instructed by Department and FEA to repeat its
                    telegram 7898, November 12 to Department to you together with our reply.<note
                        n="19" xml:id="d730fn19">Telegrams No. 7898, November 12, 9 p.m., and No.
                        7367, November 20, midnight, <ref target="#pg_816">pp. 816</ref> and <ref
                            target="#pg_819">819</ref>, respectively.</note> These communications
                    outline proposed <pb facs="0834" n="822" xml:id="pg_822"/> joint protest by you
                    and British colleague on high iron ore export rate during 1943. Unless you see
                    most important reasons making action unwise you are requested to deliver the
                    proposed memorandum to the Swedes as soon as the text from London is received
                    and parallel instructions have been received by the British Minister. Your
                    action in this matter should be reported.</p>
                <p>Reference your 3539 of October 29 and 3733 of November 16.<note n="20"
                        xml:id="d730fn20">Neither printed.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
